  <discussion>Pinus leiophylla var. chihuahuana is one of the few pines that produce sprouts from stumps. It differs from the type variety in its dark, less roughened bark, its shorter range of leaf length, and its slightly broader leaves that occur more consistently in threes. (The narrower, often longer leaves of the type variety are in fours and fives.)</discussion>
  <discussion>The type variety, Pinus leiophylla var. leiophylla , is exclusively Mexican.</discussion>
